K has a few online communities with varying sizes.

== Chat ==
* [https://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/90748/the-k-tree the k tree] - A StackExchange based chat room which has the most regular visitors. Requires 20 reputation on the site. You can contact [http://razetime.github.io/contact.html Razetime] to request entry.
* The APL Farm([https://discord.gg/qb4NXP4tKw Discord], [https://app.element.io/#/room/#aplfarm:matrix.org Matrix]) - Chatrooms for discussing APL/J/K family languages. More than 300 members as of January 2022.
* <code>#kq</code> on irc.libera.chat is frequented by a few K and Q users, but is not very active.

== Mail groups ==
* [https://groups.google.com/g/shaktidb/ Shakti Official group] Active and frequented by Shakti employees, including [[Arthur Whitney]]. Primarily focuses on K9.
* [https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/kona-user Kona users group] mostly discusses the K3 dialect, but allows discussion of K in general.
* [https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/kona-dev Kona dev group]
